name: UDUPI HOTEL - Costal Palate

reviews.review_text:
We found the restaurant's pamphlet in our room. We ordered chicken noodles, chicken biryani and tandoori full.

The packaging is decent and the food is tasty. The portion size is satisfactory as well. The food is delivered faster than expected. The pricing is reasonable as well.

Please check the menu is attached in the pics.

During our stay in south goa ( patnam) we visited this hotel for dinner and breakfast. For our dinner we ordered chicken hot garlic, chicken biryani and  chicken fried rice. Portion is good. One biryani is sufficient for one person. Taste is good. We ordered chicken hot garlic dry but it comes wet with gravy/salad only. Taste is good. Next day we visited for breakfast and ordered masala dosa, set dosa and kesari bath. Dosa is fried properly. Samabar taste is good. Chutney taste can be improved. Chutney was prepared with coconut which taste okay. This can be improved. Overall taste and price are good and affordable. I will suggest to visit this place.

Udupi Costal palate is one of the best restaurants in South Goa, where we had food..
We liked it so much that we visited next day for lunch after our dinner the previous night..

Fish Masala fry was simply delicious..Also tried Idli - it was as good as in south (Mysuru/Bengaluru). Even had Chapati and Gravy.. quantity of gravy was huge (sufficient for 4)

Overall, a must visit restaurant- especially if you are near Palolem..
Expect only good food and service .. No frills like fancy vibe, etc..
Good part is it is very economical..!

Must try King fish masala fry, Idli, Dosa..

description:
### Udupi Hotel - Coastal Palate: A Culinary Gem in Goa

Nestled in the vibrant heart of South Goa, **Udupi Hotel - Coastal Palate** boasts an impressive rating of **4.6** from **1,221** reviews, establishing itself as a must-visit destination for both locals and tourists alike. With a selection of mouthwatering **Goan food**, including standout offerings like **fish thali**, **chicken biryani**, and comforting staples such as **puri bhaji**, this eatery promises a delightful exploration of coastal cuisine.

### Ambiance & Design

Stepping into Udupi Hotel, guests are greeted by a no-frills atmosphere that focuses on comfort and simplicity. While the décor reflects a rustic charm characteristic of Goan dining, the true essence lies in its warm and inviting environment. Soft, ambient lighting casts a welcoming glow, complemented by traditional artwork that immerses diners in local culture. Although the reviews do not specifically mention music, the cozy setting seems perfect for relaxed conversations over a hearty meal, making it an ideal spot for family gatherings or casual dates.

### Menu & Culinary Experience

Udupi Hotel’s menu is a treasure trove of South Indian and Goan dishes. Signature offerings include **fish masala fry**, which patrons rave about for its flavorful and crispy finish, and the highly praised **chicken biryani**, known for its generous portion sizes that leave diners satisfied. Reviewers enthusiastically recommend the **idli**, highlighting its authenticity reminiscent of the renowned dishes in Mysuru and Bengaluru. The **masala dosa**, coupled with a deliciously thick sambhar, offers a classic breakfast option that resonates with many local tastes. It’s evident that there's something for everyone, with an array of choices catering to both vegetarian and non-vegetarian preferences.

Visually, the food presentation is thoughtful, featuring vibrant colors that encapsulate the essence of Goan cuisine. Diners can expect to see vibrant dishes, nicely garnished, as reflected in the customer images that showcase the attention to detail in plating.

### Customer Experience & Service

Customer feedback praises the staff for their friendliness and efficiency, enhancing the overall dining experience. The restaurant's service is commendably quick, with several reviews noting that food is delivered faster than anticipated—ideal for those eager to savor their meals. Many guests appreciate the reasonable pricing, making it an accessible choice for budget-conscious food lovers. Although specific details on reservation policies were not highlighted, the general sentiment suggests an accommodating approach to both walk-in and reserved guests.

### Popularity & Reviews

The overwhelming positivity surrounding Udupi Hotel is apparent in the numerous testimonials from satisfied diners. With frequent mentions of delectable **Goan food**, the establishment has gained popularity both on social media and through word-of-mouth recommendations, further solidifying its reputation as a culinary hotspot in Goa. While reviews are generally enthusiastic, constructive suggestions about improving the chutney served with idlis indicate the restaurant's commitment to feedback and continuous improvement.

### Utilizing Visual Content

The allure of Udupi Hotel is well-captured through customer-provided images that showcase both the restaurant’s inviting ambiance and the tantalizingly presented dishes. The crisp **fish masala fry**, depicted in diners' photos, reveals a golden-brown hue that hints at its flavorful crunch, while images of classic **masala dosa** and generous biryani portions portray a vibrant spread worth indulging in. Each visual element reinforces the restaurant's appeal as a culinary destination focusing on quality and authentic flavors.

### Conclusion

In summary, **Udupi Hotel - Coastal Palate** serves as a delightful portal into the world of Goan cuisine, where simplicity meets flavor in a warm, welcoming environment. With its impressive offerings, dedicated service, and attracting ambiance, it stands out as a culinary gem that should not be overlooked during your time in Goa. Whether you're in the mood for a hearty lunch or a soothing breakfast, this restaurant promises to deliver an exceptional dining experience that keeps patrons returning for more.
